commitResults.messageTitle: Implement a skeletal version of Duke that starts by greeting the user, simply echos commands entered by the user, and exits when the user types 'bye'
Add the ability to store whatever text entered by the user and display them back to the user when requested.
Add the ability to mark tasks as done. Optionally, add the ability to change the status back to not done.
Add support for tracking three types of tasks: todo, deadline and event
Handle various errors such as incorrect inputs entered by the user.
Add support for deleting tasks from the list.
Use the input/output redirection technique to semi-automate the testing of Duke.
Save the tasks in the hard disk automatically whenever the task list changes. Load the data from the hard disk when Duke starts up.

Store deadline dates as a java.time.LocalDate in task objects. Accept dates in a format such as yyyy-mm-dd format (e.g., 2019-10-15) and print in a different format such as MMM dd yyyy e.g., (Oct 15 2019).
Fix unable to parse date when it has surrounding whitespace
Organise the classes into suitable java packages.

Extract the following classes: Ui: deals with interactions with the user Storage: deals with loading tasks from the file and saving tasks in the file Parser: deals with making sense of the user command TaskList: contains the task list e.g., it has operations to add/delete tasks in the list Command classes (i.e., AddCommand, DeleteCommand, ExitCommand etc.) that inherit from an abstract Command class,
